        "old_string": "      \"id\": \"35\",\n      \"title\": \"Calendar View\",\n      \"description\": \"A new cross-project Calendar view that shows all tasks organized by their due date. Accessible from the sidebar between My Day and Projects (\\u23182). Supports both monthly grid and weekly layout with a toggle.\\n\\n**Sidebar & Navigation:**\\n- Add 'Calendar' to sidebar after My Day with Calendar icon from lucide-react\\n- Keyboard shortcut \\u23182 \\u2014 bump Projects to \\u23183+, Archive to \\u23184, Templates to \\u23185\\n- Add 'calendar' to ViewId type and VIEW_ORDER in viewStore.ts\\n- Add conditional render in AppLayout.tsx\\n\\n**Monthly View:**\\n- Classic 7-column grid (Mon\\u2013Sun), each cell lists tasks due that day\\n- Navigate months with left/right arrow buttons in the header\\n- Today highlighted with accent color/border\\n- Each task shows: colored project dot + title (truncated if long)\\n- Done tasks show strikethrough + muted text\\n- Overdue tasks (past due, not done) show in red\\n\\n**Weekly View:**\\n- 7-day horizontal columns with more vertical space per day\\n- Scrollable if many tasks\\n- Navigate weeks with left/right arrow buttons\\n- Same task display as monthly\\n\\n**Toggle:**\\n- Month/Week toggle button in the header area\\n- Persist the user's choice via settings store (key: 'calendar_layout')\\n\\n**Interactions:**\\n- Click task \\u2192 select it and open detail panel (same as project views)\\n- Drag task between day cells \\u2192 updates due_date to the target day\\n- Right-click task \\u2192 context menu (same as other views)\\n\\n**Scope:**\\n- Cross-project: shows ALL non-archived, non-template tasks that have a due_date\\n- Project color dot on each task for identification\\n- Tasks without due_date do NOT appear\\n\\n**Empty States:**\\n- Days with no tasks: empty cell\\n- No tasks with due dates at all: centered empty state message\\n\\n**Files to create/modify:**\\n- Create `src/renderer/src/features/views/Ca