Story #36 is complete. Story #37 (Due Date Notifications) still has `passes: false`, so exiting normally for the next call.

**Summary of what was built:**

- **`ProjectTemplateTask.due_date_offset`** — new `number | null` field in the shared type
- **Save flow** — `buildTaskTree` computes day offsets from task due dates relative to today. The wizard shows a "Due Dates" step (only when tasks have due dates) with a toggle to include/exclude offsets and a preview of the computed offsets
- **Deploy flow** — The wizard shows a "Due Dates" step (only when template has offsets) with a date picker defaulting to today and a preview of computed actual dates
- **`createTaskTree`** — applies `due_date = deployDate + offset` when creating tasks from template
- **Utilities** — Extracted `dueDateOffsets.ts` with `computeOffset`, `computeDateFromOffset`, `formatOffset`, `collectTasksWithOffsets`, `stripOffsets`
- **Tests** — 24 unit tests covering all utility functions
- **Backward compatible** — existing templates without `due_date_offset` are treated as null (no due dates step shown)
